{
  "text": "There are at least two reasons why rare plants in general, and P. penlandii in particular, may depend as much on pollinators as do common plants. First, if the decline in the number and size of populations is for anthropogenic reasons, as is frequently suspected [CITATION_1] , that decline may be too rapid and too recent for a breeding system response to be evident. Current evidence seems not to require such an explantion: flowers of many rare plants including P.",
